{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Abolish the Minimum Income Floor in Universal Credit.",
        "additional_details": "We think the Government should revoke clause 62 of the Universal Credit Regulations 2013 which assumes people who are \u201cgainfully\u201d self-employed have a minimum level of earnings for the purpose of calculating universal credit. We think the MIF should be abolished, which could ensure the self-employed do not disproportionately face poverty and hardship.",
        "background": "We think the Minimum Income Floor (MIF) is weighted against self-employed people and is incompatible with the fluctuating nature of the creative self-employment industry. We think it drives people away from the creative arts and into lower-skilled work.",
